&lt;p&gt;Combine sugar, butter and corn syrup in a small saucepan; cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly. Pour syrup mixture into a 13x9x2&amp;quot; baking dish. Place 6 slices of bread on top of syrup mixture. Top with remaining 6 slices of bread.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Combine eggs, milk, vanilla, and salt, stirring until blended. Pour egg mixture evenly over bread slices. Cover and chill 8 hours. Bake, uncovered at 350 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Source:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Forest Manor. 415 Cold Springs Road Rd. Napa Valley Wine Country. Angwin, CA 94508; (707) 965-3538&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

